summary: This is a U.S. Department of Justice Office of the Inspector General evidence custody document, recording the seizure of property. The form is partially filled but contains redacted or illegible information regarding the specific case, location, items seized, and personnel involved.
keyFacts: The document is an official DOJ OIG evidence custody form (OIG Form III-234/I).
The form records a property seizure, but key fields like the case number, date, location, item description, and names of witnesses/seizing agents are redacted or illegible.
The form version date is 04/23/07, indicating it was in use from at least that date.
